details:
Case 130 is a 66 year-old male Singapore Citizen who has no recent travel history to affected countries and regions. He is a family member of Case 129, and is linked to the cluster involving the private dinner function at SAFRA Jurong.

He reported onset of symptoms on 24 February and had sought treatment at a GP clinic on the same day, and on 29 February and 1 March. He presented at Ng Teng Fong General Hospital on 4 March. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 6 March morning.

Prior to hospital admission, he had gone to work at Jurong Port Road Food Centre as a food handler, and visited Bukit Batok Community Club (21 Bukit Batok Central). He stays at Jurong West Street 71.
